cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.NE

This paper uses natural language processing (NLP) techniques and neural models to classify and analyze linguistic characteristics of Alzheimer's disease patients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper performs automatic pattern discovery, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry and Topology). Lastly, the paper uses neural models to classify gender-separated AD data, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
